SIMPLE: whipper
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Whipper
<hw>Whip"per</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>One who whips; especially, an officer who inflicts
the penalty of legal whipping.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who raises coal or merchandise with a tackle
from a chip's hold.</def> <mark>[Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Spinning)</fld> <def>A kind of simple
willow.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Whipperin</ent>⟦br⟧
